  "text": "The white-box Jacobian-based saliency map approach (JSMA) was introduced in [CITATION_1] . The method iteratively perturbs features of the input that have large adversarial saliency scores. Intuitively, this score reflects the adversarial goal of taking a sample away from its source class towards a chosen target class.",
